name: Dava Rizki Andri
review_text: Explore the amazing historical heritage! The Taj Mahal reveals the beauty of classical Indian architectural art. It was built in the 17th century by Maharaja Shah Jahan to immortalize his eternal love for his wife. Be enchanted by the luxurious white dome and stunning ornate carvings . The calm and loving atmosphere around this area is sure to amaze your heart. Witness the beauty of the sunset bathed in gold attached to this iconic building. An unforgettable experience that amazes and inspires! Make sure this destination is on your travel list! #TajMahal #WorldWonder

name: Kei
review_text:
I drove from Delhi on a tour I had booked in advance.

The English speaking tour guide told me that the entrance ticket was 3000 rupees, but after checking the information online in advance, I told him that it wouldnt cost that much and I would buy it myself at the ticket office.

If I bought it myself, it would have cost 1100 rupees.
Instead, I was told that there was an additional fee to go inside the Taj Mahal, so I didnt go in, but when I saw it later on Youtube, it didnt seem like there was a separate fee. Even after leaving India, I still dont understand.

The Taj Mahal, one of the seven most mysterious wonders of the world, is a must-visit spot.

name: rajesh jaiswar
review_text:
The Taj Mahal is a white marble mausoleum built by Emperor Shah Jahan for his second wife, Mumtaz Mahal, who died in childbirth in 1631. For the story behind its construction, it is axiomatic to say that it is one of the greatest monuments to love ever built. Thousands of workers labored for over 20 years on the building, embellishing it with outstanding decorations including white marble screens and pietra dura inlay with semiprecious stones. At over 200 feet (60 meters) tall, the structure is the tallest Mughal tomb ever built and is considered to be the single greatest work of Mughal architecture. It is the centerpiece of a sprawling complex of buildings, courtyards, gardens, and waterways on the edge of the river Yamuna in Agra. Most of this original landscape is intact.

The Taj has long been recognized for its outstanding beauty and architectural merit, and has been a UNESCO World Heritage Site since 1982. It is one of the national symbols of India and receives millions of visitors every year. As with similarly famous, popular, and fragile sites around the world, this huge influx of tourists imperils the physical fabric of the monument. In addition, although new industrial development in Agra has been banned and only non-polluting vehicles are allowed near the Taj, environmental degradation is still a major concern for the conservation of the mausoleum and the structures that surround it. In 1996 in a historic judgement the Supreme Court of India ordered measures to preserve and protect the environments of Agra to safeguard the Taj Mahal's marble facade.

Many might have query whether Tajmahal opens in early hours or not, So here is the answer it opens 30mins before sunrise so you can ensure reaching there at early hours to avoid extreme hot weather in day time. Ticket booking counter also opens before sunrise. I would suggest to take an official guide as it is very helpful and it ensures that we are not getting cheated by any local fraud and it make sense as they bring good information about the places which we cannot get by our own. Battery vehicle are available from car parking/ booking centre to Tajmahal. Tajmahal is closed on Friday.

name: CR SIYAG
review_text:
Taj Mahal needs no introduction. This monument is included in the list of seven wonders of the world. No wonder people flock to it throughout the year to witness the grandeur of its beauty. This monument is located in the city of Agra, Uttar Pradesh in India. In other words, the Taj Mahal symbolizes the excellence of Mughal architecture.

essay on Taj Mahal

Taj Mahal is one of the main reasons why India is famous. Many people associate India with the Taj Mahal. However, for me, more than the spectacular architecture, it is the story behind it that fascinates me the most. This magnificent beauty stands strong as a symbol of a husbands love for his wife. Furthermore, it reminds us of the power of love and how it can set an example for future generations.

Taj Maha - Symbol of Love
The famous Taj Mahal was brought to life from the vision of Mughal emperor Shah Jahan. He built this memorial for his beloved wife Mumtaz Mahal after her death.

To honor the memory of his beloved wife, Shah Jahan ordered the finest artisans from around the world to create it. He wanted to create something that had never been created for anyone before. The king wanted to give his last gift to his wife whom he loved very much.

Weekday

Reservation recommended
Yes

1. Basic ticket  180
2. Mausoleum entry.  250
Carrying any one of the Id proof for security check is must.
No eatables are allowed inside the premises. If found they will throw them away before entering.
Monkey menace is a big problem. There are warning and guidelines to tackle them.

Security is tight here. Tourists are not allowed to carry big bags . Only small bag with water bottles, purse etc is allowed.

name: Heera Rawani
review_text:
The Taj Mahal is an iconic white marble mausoleum located in Agra, Uttar Pradesh, India. It was commissioned by the Mughal emperor Shah Jahan in 1631 to house the tomb of his beloved wife, Mumtaz Mahal. The Taj Mahal stands as a testament to love and is recognized as the jewel of Muslim art in India and one of the universally admired masterpieces of the worlds heritage.

Here are some key facts about the Taj Mahal:
Location It is situated on the right bank of the river Yamuna in Agra
Construction The construction of the mausoleum was completed in 1648, but the entire complex was completed in 1653
Architecture The Taj Mahal is a prime example of Mughal architecture, combining elements from Indian, Persian, and Islamic influences3.
Complex The 17-hectare complex includes a mosque, a guest house, and is set in formal gardens bounded on three sides by a crenellated wall.
It attracts more than five million visitors a year and was declared a winner of the New 7 Wonders of the World initiative in 2007

The Taj Mahal is not just a historical monument but also a symbol of the rich cultural heritage of India. Its open for visitors except on Fridays, and the visiting hours are 30 minutes before sunrise up to 30 minutes before sunset2. If youre planning a visit, its truly a sight to behold and a marvel of architectural beauty.

name: Sarath Krishnan S
review_text:
As you step into the city of Agra, the air is filled with the scent of history and culture.
Rising before dawn, you can make your way to the entrance of the Taj Mahal, as it will be open at 6.00 Am. As the sun begins to rise, the Taj emerges from the mist, casting a spellbinding reflection on the tranquil waters of the reflecting pool. Walking through the ornate gate, you will be greeted by the sight of the mausoleum standing majestically against the azure sky.

The meticulously manicured gardens, is a symmetrical beauty that surrounds the monument. The lush greenery, interspersed with vibrant blooms, creates a sense of serenity and tranquility, contrasting with the grandeur of the marble monument at its heart.

Approaching the main mausoleum, you will awestruck by its sheer size and intricate detailing. While looking at a photo or distance we wont understand the enormousity of that structure due to its square base. As you ascend the steps, the marble facade reveals its delicate carvings and inlaid gemstones, each telling a story of love and devotion. Inside, the cenotaphs of Shah Jahan and Mumtaz Mahal lie side by side, a testament to their eternal bond.

Adjacent to the main mausoleum, the mosque and guest house stand as architectural marvels in their own right. The symmetry between the two structures is mesmerizing, with intricate marble lattice work adorning every surface. The Yamuna was dried up at that time as it was summer.

.

name: God Seeker
review_text: Taj Mahal, a UNESCO World Heritage Site, is an architectural masterpiece nestled in the heart of Agra, India. Built by Emperor Shah Jahan in memory of his beloved wife Mumtaz Mahal, this iconic monument captivates visitors with its symmetrical beauty and exquisite details. The shimmering white marble facade, adorned with intricate carvings and inlaid precious stones, reflects the grandeur of Mughal architecture. As you wander through the lush gardens and marvel at the reflection pools, you cant help but be swept away by the romance and history that permeate the air. A visit to the Taj Mahal is a journey through time, where every corner reveals a story of love, craftsmanship, and enduring legacy.

name: Deepesh Solanki
review_text:
In that first glimpse of the Taj Mahal, you will be transported to another time and place, where beauty and devotion have no bounds. It is a moment that will stay with you forever

As you approach the Taj Mahal for the first time, the anticipation builds with every step closer to its grand entrance. The air is heavy with a sense of reverence.

Passing through the threshold, you find yourself standing at the edge of a vast expanse of perfectly manicured gardens.

The sound of flowing water from marble fountains fills the air, lending a soothing rhythm to the atmosphere.

And then, as you turn the corner, there it is, The Taj Mahal in all its splendor

As you draw closer, you can see the delicate details carved into every inch of the structure, from the intricate marble lattice screens to the delicate inlay work of precious gemstones.

The intricate patterns of floral motifs and geometric designs across its surface catching the light is a mesmerizing display of craftsmanship.

#IncredibleIndia
#WondersOfTheWorld
#IconicArchitecture
#EternalLoveStory
#AgraDiaries
#IndiaOdyssey
#GlimpseOfHistory
#CaptivatingTaj

name: Asha Stephen
review_text:
One among the architectural wonders of the world and the most incredible place in India . Its a must visit place to see when visiting India

Located in Agra,uttar pradesh this cultural and historical monument is undoubtedly mesmerizing .Best time to visit is morning or evening so that you can relax and enjoy the beauty the place has to offer .
Gov. approved photographers are available at affordable rates. And best time for photography will be in the before noon as it will be less crowded that time.
The place is accessible by metro,
flight( Agra Airport), train( Agra Cantt)
and bus.
And its better for tourists to take Ola,Uber instead of getting scammed by local taxi people.
Entry fee is Rs.50 & 250 to get inside taj mahal .Rate is different for foreigners.Tickets can be taken online also.
There is also free cloak room inside and food items are not allowed inside.

Public toilet was awful not at all clean despite charging money to access it,They have not maintained it well.

name: Matt T
review_text:
A once in a lifetime must see location/monument. The aura of the Taj Mahal is tangible and something you don't experience in many places globally.

Highly recommend choosing to either view at sunrise 6-6:20 am (which we did) or doing a sunset visit. We also had a guide arranged through our hotel (Mohsin) who was incredibly knowledgeable, spoke perfect English and handled all elements of ticketing (~PS10pp) / queuing / taxi and transport.

Once we arrived at 6am there was a pretty chaotic queue to get onto an electric buggy as the Taj Mahal area is a low emission zone.

Arriving at the entry gate after securing our tickets there is a short walk through one of the gates before you start to see the Taj Mahal and enter via the main gate.

The aura of the Taj Mahal can be felt instantly, the beauty of the building is incredible as are the surrounding areas such as the gardens and water features. Spend time to soak it in and naturally you will have to deal with 100s of tourists taking photos so I recommend taking a step back and appreciating it for what it is (also why the earlier you visit the better)!

Enjoy some time in the gardens and the short walk to the Taj. Once there you will need to wear shoe covers and you can enter and walk around inside in a guarded circle. This gives you some time to appreciate the craftsmanship, the design and the cultural heritage. Once you leave you have a view from either side as well as being able to see Agra Fort in the distance.

An incredible experience and one not to be missed!

Note the Taj is open every day of the week between sunrise and sunset, except Fridays, when it is only open in the afternoon when people are attending the Taj Mosque for prayers.

name: Mohit Chopra
review_text:
What can I say about the Taj which hasnt already been said. Taj is breathtaking. It is cleverly hidden from the view when you approach it either from the West gate or the east gate. It is only when you cross the red stone entry gate (which is beautiful on its own) that it suddenly appears in its full grandeur. One cannot help but take out a camera and click a few dozen pictures.

A couple of tips for first time visitors

1. Try to take the early morning ticket. The morning entry begins 30 minutes before sunrise and it is wonderful to watch the Taj at sunrise

2. Book tickets online. It will save you a lot of time. The tickets cost Rs 45/- for Indians and Rs 1,050/- for a foreigner.

3. If you want to enter the mausoleum its Rs 200/- more per person. Its worth it .

4. The line for foreigners is really really long so try and queue up early.

5. Kids below 15 years both Indian and Foreign, get in free

review_text: The Taj Mahal stands as a timeless testament to love and architectural grandeur. Its pristine white marble gleams under the sun, while intricate carvings and delicate inlays adorn its surfaces, telling the tale of a love that transcends time. Surrounded by lush gardens, the Taj Mahal enchants visitors with its symmetrical beauty and serene reflection pools, inviting contemplation and awe. It remains a marvel of human craftsmanship and devotion, capturing hearts and imaginations from across the globe.
